external_knowledge:
- "Top-rated materials" refers to the materials with the highest percentages of being recyclable or compostable; 
- A material is considered "recyclable" if it can be reprocessed into a new product, reducing the need to extract and process raw materials from the earth; 
- A material is considered "compostable" if it is made from organic materials and can decompose, returning to nature.

sql:
SELECT SUM(disposed_tons) as total_disposed_tons
FROM waste_composition
WHERE year = 2023 AND month = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "Recyclable materials" refers to materials with the 'recyclable' flag set to 1 in the materials table; 
- "Top 3 materials" refers to materials with the highest disposed tons in each sector;
- "Disposed tons" refers to the amount of material disposed of, measured in tons.
